The '''discography of [[Carla Bruni]]''', a italian-french singer-songwriter, consists of three [[studio]] album, five [[single (music)|singles]], six promotional singles and five [[music video]]s. In 2003, her debut album ''[[Quelqu'un m'a dit]]'', produced by [[Louis Bertignac]], was released in Europe with success in [[Francophone]] countries. Three songs from the album appear in [[Hans Canosa]]'s 2005 American film ''[[Conversations with Other Women]]'',<ref>[http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0435623/soundtrack Conversations with Other Women (2005) <U+2013> Soundtracks] <U+2013> [[Internet Movie Database|IMDb]]</ref> the song ''Le Plus Beau du quartier'' was used in [[H&M]]'s Christmas 2006 commercial, and the title track was featured in the 2003 movie ''[[Le Divorce]]''<ref>[http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0306734/soundtrack Le divorce (2003) <U+2013> Soundtracks] <U+2013> [[Internet Movie Database|IMDb]]</ref> and in the 2009 movie ''[[(500) Days of Summer]]''.<ref>[http://www.imdb.com/title/tt1022603/soundtrack (500) Days of Summer (2009) <U+2013> Soundtracks] <U+2013> [[Internet Movie Database|IMDb]]</ref>  In January 2010, her song "L'amoureuse" was featured in an episode of [[NBC]]'s ''[[Chuck (TV series)|Chuck]]'', "Chuck vs. First Class".<ref>[http://www.imdb.com/title/tt1518910/soundtrack "Chuck": Chuck Versus First Class (2010) <U+2013> Soundtracks] <U+2013> [[Internet Movie Database|IMDb]]</ref>

Her second album, ''[[No Promises (Carla Bruni album)|No Promises]]'' containing poems by [[William Butler Yeats]], [[Emily Dickinson]], [[W. H. Auden]], [[Dorothy Parker]], [[Walter de la Mare]], and [[Christina Rossetti]], set to music, was released in January 2007. She released her third album ''[[Comme si de rien n'<U+00E9>tait]]'' on 11 July 2008. The songs are self-penned except for one rendition of "[[You Belong to Me (1952 song)|You Belong to Me]]" and another song featuring [[Michel Houellebecq]]'s poem ''La Possibilit<U+00E9> d'une <U+00EE>le'' set to music.<ref name="new album">{{cite news|url=http://timescorrespondents.typepad.com/charles_bremner/2008/05/carla-brunis-ne.html| title = Carla Bruni's new pot song |first=Charles |last=Bremner| work  = The Times |location=UK |date=21 May 2008}}</ref> Royalties from the album will be donated to unidentified charitable and humanitarian cause.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.biz/bbbiz/content_display/industry/e3i152f68c2925022d5875d809a21359e64|title=Bruni's 'Promises' To Arrive This Summer |first=Lars |last=Brandle| work  = Billboard.biz |date=21 May 2008 }}</ref>

